		<!-- message -->
		<div>Air pet: Casts stun. Got good avoidance and mitigation, decent hp. <br />
<br />
Water pet: Casts a cold DD. 54+ water pets backstab. Mages LOVE tanks that know this and cares enough to let the pet backstab. If a mage is using this pet, try being consistent in where you position mobs and which direction you are facing so the mage can park his pet where it will have access to the mob's back. Mages are lazy and will appreciate it if you don't make them run more than necessary.<br />
<br />
Epic pet: Casts a 143 DD + stun, and procs 70ish DD - alot. In LDoN and other non-PoP zones this is the best dps pet. Due to the low level it attracts adds easily, and it can't really land anything on mobs in PoP. Nothing like the epic to mow down greenies tho...<br />
<br />
<br />
To answer Xerro's question:<br />
<br />
Except for the situations where the epic can be used, the water pet is the bestest dps pet. That is assuming it has a back to stab. The stuns from the air pet are usually worth more to a group, though. Also the air pet is a much better tank than the water pet.<br />
<br />
For more definate numbers on mage pets, start here:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3191" target="_blank">Magecompendium</a> <br />
<br />
Note that mage, necro and beastlord pets can have their hp, regen rate and max hit increased by focus items.<br />
<br />
<br />
Prolly more than you asked for, I'm slightly bored at work tho <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" class="inlineimg" /></div>
