		<!-- message -->
		<div>hi<br />
<br />
i have recently started an sk (lvl 16 at time of posting)<br />
<br />
My main is a lvl 65 mage on Venril Sathir server<br />
<br />
I woudl like to defend a mage using the all powerfull earth pet.  but unfortunately I cant.  Earth pet is simply not a group pet at any level (although i understand the 65 earth doesent root - i am still missing that spell - )  except for a few rare exceptions.<br />
<br />
<br />
fire pet is  a good nuker with the new kindle spell (pet kei)  and dependant on the groups level can be a good alternative,  the 63 fire aoe snares and ice commets.<br />
<br />
but in most groups i use water pet, a lvl 62 water pet positioned correctly with summoned wepons can out damage a mage epic pet.<br />
<br />
If the group will be likely to fight a good share of casters, then Its air everytime.  If i got a plat piece for every time my air pet stopped a caster in mid chant, i would be able to buy enough fungi tunics to use them as pet gear :O))<br />
<br />
I hate to say this, but if a mage is inapropriatly using an Earth pet because it "hits harder"  try sugesting that he measures time it takes to killa mob with earth for say 5 mobs, and the 5 mobs using air, hell you can give hime a couple of gold to cover the cost of the malachites.<br />
<br />
using the above mentioned test, if he is honest he will see the difference and use his air<br />
<br />
If he refuses to try or refuses to listen to the results of the test, then you should think abotu replacing him.<br />
<br />
BUT<br />
<br />
If you have no movement slower (obviously this is an SK board and SK has darkness snares)   earth pet used in group is usefull to stop mob running but it is very inportant for the main tank to get a good agro built up before pet sends in the pet.<br />
<br />
<br />
on the whole though Mages are great group members, nice dps both sustained through the pet and burst through his spells.<br />
<br />
Dont discount mages because of a few, who havent learned their class yet, it is very easy to assume that the newest pet, or the biggest pet, is the best for every situation.<br />
<br />
Thats my first installment of <br />
<br />
my 2 cp worth <br />
<br />
/bow<br />
Bolerus</div>
